14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Health – General
17 4–201.
18 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
19 (u) “Vital record” means a certificate or report of birth, death, fetal death,
20 marriage, divorce, dissolution or annulment of marriage, adoption, or adjudication of
21 paternity that is required by law to be filed with the Secretary.
22 4–217.
23 (c) (1) Except as otherwise provided by law:
24 (i) The Department shall collect a $12 fee:
25 1. For each certified or abridged copy of a fetal death,
26 marriage, or divorce verification certificate;
27 2. For a report that a search of the fetal death, marriage, or
28 divorce verification certificate files was made and the requested record is not on file;
29 3. For each change to a fetal death, marriage, or divorce
30 verification certificate made later than 1 year after the certificate has been registered with
31 the Department; or
32 4. To process an adoption, foreign adoption, or legitimation;

HOUSE BILL 1353 3
1 (ii) The Department shall collect a $10 fee:
2 1. Except as provided in paragraph (6)(ii) of this subsection,
3 for each certified or abridged copy of a birth certificate;
4 2. For the first copy of a certified or abridged death certificate
5 issued in a single transaction;
6 3. For a report that a search of the birth or death certificate
7 files was made and the requested record is not on file; or
8 4. For each change to a birth or death certificate made later
9 than 1 year after the certificate has been registered with the Department; and
10 (iii) The Department shall collect a $12 fee for each additional
11 certified or abridged copy of a death certificate provided concurrently with an initial
12 requested death certificate.
13 (2) From the fee the Department collects under paragraph (1) of this
14 subsection, the Department shall transfer the entire fee to the General Fund.
15 (3) (i) Any local health department or the Motor Vehicle
16 Administration may set and collect a fee for processing and issuing a birth certificate or
17 death certificate, or for a report that a search of the files was made and the requested record
18 is not on file, that covers:
19 1. The administrative costs of providing this service; and
20 2. The requirements of subparagraph (iii) of this paragraph.
21 (ii) The fee set by the local health department or the Motor Vehicle
22 Administration for processing and issuing a birth certificate or for a report under
23 subparagraph (i) of this paragraph may not exceed the actual costs to the local health
24 department or the Motor Vehicle Administration for processing and issuing a birth
25 certificate or death certificate or a report.
26 (iii) From the fee the local health department or the Motor Vehicle
27 Administration collects under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph, $10 shall be transferred
28 to the General Fund.
29 (iv) Prior to setting and collecting a fee for processing and issuing a
30 birth certificate or death certificate or for a report under subparagraph (i) of this paragraph,
31 the local health department or the Motor Vehicle Administration shall enter into a
32 memorandum of understanding with the Maryland Department of Health that outlines the
33 local health department’s or the Motor Vehicle Administration’s fee structure.

4 HOUSE BILL 1353
1 (4) The Department, a local health department, or the Motor Vehicle
2 Administration may collect a fee for a certificate requested by an agency of the State or any
3 of its political subdivisions.
4 (5) The Secretary may waive all or part of a fee if chargeable to an agency
5 of the United States.
6 (6) (i) The Department may not collect a fee for a copy of a vital record
7 issued to:
8 1. A current or former member of the uniformed services; or
9 2. The surviving spouse or child of the member, if the copy
10 will be used in connection with a claim for a dependent or beneficiary of the member.
11 (ii) 1. In this subparagraph, “homeless individual” has the
12 meaning stated in INCLUDES HOMELESS CHILDREN AND YOUTHS, AS DEFINED IN the
13 federal McKinney–Vento Homeless [Education] Assistance [Improvements] Act [of 2001].
14 2. Subject to subsubparagraph 4 of this subparagraph, the
15 Department may not collect a fee for a [certified or an abridged copy of a birth certificate]
16 VITAL RECORD issued to a homeless individual.
17 3. The Department shall accept as proof of homelessness a
18 signed written statement from a homeless services provider located in the State OR, AS
19 SPECIFIED IN THE FEDERAL MCKINNEY–VENTO HOMELESS ASSISTANCE ACT, A
20 LOCAL EDUCATIONAL AGENCY LIAISON OR ANY DESIGNATED SCHOOL PERSONNEL
21 that:
22 A. Affirms that the individual is homeless; and
23 B. Includes the address to which the copy of the [birth
24 certificate] VITAL RECORD requested under this section may be sent.
25 4. A homeless individual may receive one copy of a [birth
26 certificate] VITAL RECORD without a fee in a single transaction.
27 5. The Department shall adopt regulations to implement this
28 subparagraph.
29 (iii) The Department may not collect a fee for a certified or abridged
30 copy of a death certificate of a first responder, as defined in § 18–213.2 of this article, killed
31 in the line of duty, if the copy is issued to a surviving spouse or child of the first responder
32 and will be used in connection with a claim for a dependent or beneficiary of the first
33 responder.

