1 Article – Transportation
2 13–903.
3 (a) The following vehicles are exempt from the registration fees specified in this
4 subtitle:
5 (1) A vehicle that is owned and operated by the United States, this State,
6 or any political subdivision of this State;
7 (2) A vehicle that is owned by a volunteer fire company incorporated in this
8 State or by a rescue squad and that is used for firefighting or ambulance purposes;
9 (3) A canteen wagon of a recognized fire buff organization, as certified by
10 the International Fire Buffs Association;
11 (4) A vehicle owned and operated by the Civil Air Patrol;
12 (5) A vehicle owned and operated by a unit of a national veterans’
13 organization;
14 (6) A vehicle owned and operated by a Maryland chapter of the American
15 Red Cross;
16 (7) A motor vehicle and trailer known as the “40–8 box car” that is owned
17 and operated only for social or charitable purposes by any voiture of the Forty and Eight of
18 the American Legion, Department of Maryland;
19 (8) A vehicle owned by, or leased to, and personally used by a veteran who:
20 (i) As designated or classified by the U.S. Department of Veterans
21 Affairs, has lost the use of a hand, arm, or leg, or is totally disabled; or
22 (ii) Has a permanent impairment of both eyes so that:
23 1. The central visual acuity is 20/200 or less in the better eye,
24 with corrective glasses; or
25 2. There is a field defect in which the peripheral field has
26 contracted to such an extent that the widest diameter of visual field subtends an angular
27 distance no greater than 20 degrees in the better eye;
28 (9) A vehicle owned and personally used by an individual who is the
29 surviving spouse of a deceased disabled veteran, as defined under § 7–208 of the
30 Tax – Property Article; [and]

