16 (ii) Until after successful completion of:
17 1. The driver education program approved under Subtitle 5
18 of this title, consisting of at least 30 hours of classroom instruction and at least 6 hours of
19 highway driving instruction; and
20 2. At least 60 hours, 10 hours of which must occur during the
21 period beginning 30 minutes before sunset and ending 30 minutes after sunrise, of
22 behind–the–wheel driving practice supervised by an individual who:
23 A. Holds a valid driver’s license;
24 B. Is at least 21 years old; and
25 C. Has been licensed to drive for at least 3 years; and
26 (iii) Unless the individual submits, in accordance with the
27 Administration’s regulations, a completed skills log book signed by:
28 1. Each supervising driver who certifies that the individual
29 has satisfactorily demonstrated a required skill and has completed the driving practice
30 requirements of item (ii)2 of this paragraph; and

