4 (a) (1) A motor vehicle for which special registration plates have been issued
5 under § 13–616 of this article is exempt from the mandatory inspections required by this
6 subtitle if:
7 (i) All of the owners of the motor vehicle meet the disability
8 requirements of § 13–616(b)(1) of this article;
9 (ii) The motor vehicle is driven 5,000 miles or less annually; and
10 (iii) The exemption is not otherwise prohibited by federal law.
11 (2) In order to qualify for an exemption under paragraph (1) of this
12 subsection, all owners of the motor vehicle shall certify the following:
13 (i) That the owner of the motor vehicle meets the disability
14 requirements of § 13–616(b)(1) of this article;
15 (ii) That the motor vehicle has been issued a special disabled
16 person’s registration number and special registration plates under § 13–616 of this article;
17 (iii) That the motor vehicle is driven 5,000 miles or less annually; and
18 (iv) The motor vehicle’s odometer reading at the time of the
19 certification.
20 (3) The certification required in paragraph (2) of this subsection shall be
21 made on a form provided by the Administration.
22 (b) (1) A motor vehicle owned by an individual who is at least 70 years of age
23 at the time of a scheduled mandatory inspection under this subtitle is exempt from the
24 mandatory inspections required by this subtitle if:
25 (i) All of the owners of the motor vehicle are at least 70 years of age
26 at the time of the scheduled mandatory inspection under this subtitle;
27 (ii) The motor vehicle is being driven 5,000 miles or less annually;
28 and
29 (iii) The exemption is not otherwise prohibited by federal law.
30 (2) In order to qualify for an exemption under paragraph (1) of this
31 subsection, all owners of the motor vehicle shall certify the following:

